In a statement on the International Day Against Homophobia and Transphobia, the Vice President emphasizes the importance of treating everyone with dignity and respect. He acknowledges the difficulties the LGBT community has faced over the years but also highlights the progress that has been made towards equality in the United States. However, he notes that in many places around the world, life for LGBT individuals is actually deteriorating, with violence, mistreatment, and discrimination still prevalent. The Vice President calls for supportive voices to speak up in favor of universal human rights and defends the rights of LGBT people, stating that everyone deserves dignity, respect, and equal treatment under the law.